   <abstract displayLabel="Description">Merritt discusses other units leaving the Camp to guard hospitals in Baltimore. He describes sickness and religious services in the Camp.</abstract>
   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">John Merritt was a Union soldier from Madison County, New York. He enlisted as a private on August 9, 1862, Company D, 114th Regiment infantry, New York Volunteers.  He served in several Louisiana campaigns. He was probably wounded in the battle of Opequon, Va., September 19, 1864.  He was mustered out on June 8, 1865.</note>
